  "texts": [
    "The number of options that are offered in an assortment can be obtained by summing over all x i, i.e.",
    "∑ i∈N x i.",
    "The demand for any option depends on the preferences of the customers and is captured by a choice model specifying the probability that a customer selects a particular option from a given offer set as detailed in Sect. 3.",
    "Assuming a general choice model-i.e.",
    "any arbitrary choice model such as the multinomial logit, the nested logit, the Markov chain choice, or the rank-based model without specifying a particular one (Talluri and van Ryzin 2004; Gallego and Topaloglu 2019; Strauss et al. 2018)-the customer selects alternative i ∈ N with probability p i (x) given that assortment x is offered and decides to not purchase anything with probability p 0 (x)."
  ],
